A '''chief brand officer''' ('''CBO''') is a relatively new executive-level position at a corporation, company, organization, or agency, which typically reports to the [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] or [[board of directors]] and is responsible for a [[brand]]'s image, experience, and promise. The brand officer oversees [[marketing]], [[advertising]], [[design]], [[public relations]], and [[customer service]].<ref>Neumeier, Marty (2006). The Brand Gap: How to Bridge the Distance Between Business Strategy and Design, Berkeley, CA : New Riders Publishing.</ref><ref>Scott Bedbury, Stephen Fenichell. (2003), A New Brand World: 8 Principles for Achieving Brand Leadership in the 21st Century. Penguin.</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Who is the brand daddy?|url=http://www.landor.com/pdfs/k9/AWelch_BrandDaddy_26Mar08.pdf|work=Brand Strategy|publisher=[[Landor Associates]]|accessdate=15 October 2012|author=Andrew Welch|date=March 2008|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131007215924/http://www.landor.com/pdfs/k9/AWelch_BrandDaddy_26Mar08.pdf|archivedate=7 October 2013|df=}}</ref> Some of the more notable organizations to establish a CBO position include the [[American Automobile Association]], ElevenUp Group, [[Baskin-Robbins]], [[Bell Canada]], [[Boston Market]], [[Citigroup]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Citigroup appoints chief brand officer|url=http://www.bankingtimes.co.uk/2011/03/17/citigroup-appoints-chief-brand-officer/|accessdate=15 October 2012|newspaper=Banking Times|date=March 17, 2011|location=London}}</ref> [[McDonald's]],<ref>{{cite news|title=McDonald's Names Brand Chief|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748703399204576108410917398584|accessdate=15 October 2012|newspaper=Wall Street Journal|date=January 27, 2011}}</ref> [[WWE]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Johnson|first=Joe|title=Stephanie McMahon Promotion Leaves Triple H in Charge of WWE Creative|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/1877506-stephanie-mcmahon-promotion-leaves-triple-h-in-charge-of-wwe-creative|accessdate=5 December 2013|newspaper=Bleacher Report|date=5 December 2013}}</ref> and [[Mattel]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Mattel Appoints Richard Dickson Chief Brands Officer|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/mattel-appoints-richard-dickson-chief-brands-officer-2014-05-19?reflink=MW_news_stmp|accessdate=May 19, 2014|newspaper=Market Watch|date=May 19, 2014}}</ref>
