{{About|the Egyptian businessman and politician|the Egyptian linguist|El-Said Badawi}}
{{Infobox Officeholder | name = El-Sayyid el-Badawi | image = El-Sayyid el-Badawi.jpg | office = Chairperson of the [[New Wafd Party]] | term_start = 28 May 2010 | predecessor = Mahmoud Abaza | birth_date = 1950 | birth_place = [[Tanta]], [[Egypt]] | party = [[New Wafd Party|Al-Wafd Party]] | religion = [[Sunni Islam]] }}
'''El-Sayyid el-Badawi Shehata''' ({{lang-arz|السيد البدوى شحاتة}}, {{IPA-arz|es-, el ˈsæjːed el ˈbædæwi ʃeˈħæːtæ|IPA}}) (born 1950) is an [[Egypt]]ian businessman and the President of [[New Wafd Party|Al-Wafd Party]]. He graduated from the Faculty of Pharmacy of the [[University of Alexandria]] in 1973.<ref>[http://www.alwafdparty.com/details.aspx?t=man&id=1714 Dr. El-Sayyid el-Badawi] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101112022945/http://www.alwafdparty.com/details.aspx?t=man&id=1714 |date=2010-11-12 }}, Wafd Party website</ref> He is the head of the Board of Directors of Al-Hayah Egyptian television network.<ref>[http://dostor.org/politics/egypt/10/may/4/15200 Fouad Badrawi give up running for the presidency of Al-Wafd Party in favor of El-Sayyid el-Badawi], [[Al-Dustour (Egypt)|Al-Dustour]]</ref>
